==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gregory
<hw>Gregory</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def><person>Pope
Gregory XIII.</person>, born 1572, died 1585, the pope who introduced
the modern calendar.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Gregory XIII, Ugo Buoncompagni.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def><person>Pope Gregory I.</person>, born circa 540,
died 604; the pope for whom Gregorian chants were named.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Gregory I, Saint Gregory I, Gregory the
Great.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Greillade</ent>⟦br⟧
